594 /*FUNCTION**********************************************************************
595  *
596  * Function Name : CLOCK_DRV_Init
597  * Description : This function sets the system to target configuration, it
598  * only sets the clock modules registers for clock mode change, but not send
599  * notifications to drivers.
600  *
601  * Implements CLOCK_DRV_Init_Activity
602  * END**************************************************************************/
603 status_t CLOCK_DRV_Init(clock_manager_user_config_t const * config)
604 {
605  status_t result;
606  clock_manager_user_config_t config_default;
607  clock_manager_user_config_t const * cfg = config;
608 
609  DEV_ASSERT(CLOCK_SYS_GetCurrentRunMode() == SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_MODE_RUN);
610 
611  if (config == NULL)
612  {
613  /* Get default configuration */
614  CLOCK_SYS_GetDefaultConfiguration(&config_default);
615  cfg = &config_default;
616  }
617 
618  /* Set SCG settings. */
619  result = CLOCK_SYS_SetScgConfiguration(&cfg->scgConfig);
620 
621  if (STATUS_SUCCESS == result)
622  {
623  /* Set SIM settings. */
624  CLOCK_SYS_SetSimConfiguration(&cfg->simConfig);
625 
626  /* Set PCC settings. */
627  CLOCK_SYS_SetPccConfiguration(&cfg->pccConfig);
628 
629  /* Set PMC settings. */
630  CLOCK_SYS_SetPmcConfiguration(&cfg->pmcConfig);
631  }
632 
633  return result;
634 }
635 
636 /*FUNCTION**********************************************************************
637  *
638  * Function Name : CLOCK_SYS_SetScgConfiguration
639  * Description : This function configures the SCG blocks
640  *
641  * END**************************************************************************/
642 static status_t CLOCK_SYS_SetScgConfiguration(const scg_config_t * scgConfig)
643 {
644  status_t status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
645  DEV_ASSERT(scgConfig != NULL);
646 
647  if (scgConfig != NULL)
648  {
649  /* Configure a temporary system clock source: FIRC */
650  status = CLOCK_SYS_ConfigureTemporarySystemClock();
651 
652  if (status == STATUS_SUCCESS)
653  {
654  /* Configure clock sources from SCG */
655  status = CLOCK_SYS_ConfigureModulesFromScg(scgConfig);
656  }
657 
658  if (status == STATUS_SUCCESS)
659  {
660  g_RtcClkInFreq = 0U; /* reset the value RTC_clk frequency. */
661  if (scgConfig->rtcConfig.initialize)
662  {
663  /* RTC Clock settings. */
664  g_RtcClkInFreq = scgConfig->rtcConfig.rtcClkInFreq;
665  }
666 
667  /* Configure SCG ClockOut. */
668  if (scgConfig->clockOutConfig.initialize)
669  {
670  /* ClockOut settings. */
671  SCG_SetClockoutSourceSel(SCG, (uint32_t)scgConfig->clockOutConfig.source);
672  }
673 
674  /* Configure SCG clock modes. */
675  if (scgConfig->clockModeConfig.initialize)
676  {
677  /* Configure SCG clock modes */
678  status = CLOCK_SYS_SetSystemClockConfig(SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_MODE_RUN, &(scgConfig->clockModeConfig.rccrConfig));
679  if (status == STATUS_SUCCESS)
680  {
681  status = CLOCK_SYS_SetSystemClockConfig(SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_MODE_VLPR, &(scgConfig->clockModeConfig.vccrConfig));
682  }
683 
684 #if FEATURE_HAS_HIGH_SPEED_RUN_MODE
685  if (status == STATUS_SUCCESS)
686  {
687  status = CLOCK_SYS_SetSystemClockConfig(SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_MODE_HSRUN, &(scgConfig->clockModeConfig.hccrConfig));
688  }
689 #endif
690  }
691  }
692  }
693 
694  return status;
695 }

697 /*FUNCTION**********************************************************************
698  *
699  * Function Name : CLOCK_SYS_SetPccConfiguration
700  * Description : This function configures the PCC block
701  *
702  * END**************************************************************************/
703 static void CLOCK_SYS_SetPccConfiguration(const pcc_config_t * peripheralClockConfig)
704 {
705  DEV_ASSERT(peripheralClockConfig != NULL);
706 
707  uint32_t i;
708 
709  if ((peripheralClockConfig != NULL) && (peripheralClockConfig->peripheralClocks != NULL))
710  {
711  for (i = 0U; i < peripheralClockConfig->count; i++)
712  {
713  /* Disable the peripheral clock */
714  PCC_SetClockMode(PCC, peripheralClockConfig->peripheralClocks[i].clockName, false);
715 
716  /* Set peripheral clock control */
717  PCC_SetPeripheralClockControl(PCC,
718  peripheralClockConfig->peripheralClocks[i].clockName,
719  peripheralClockConfig->peripheralClocks[i].clkGate,
720  (uint32_t)peripheralClockConfig->peripheralClocks[i].clkSrc,
721  (uint32_t)peripheralClockConfig->peripheralClocks[i].divider,
722  (uint32_t)peripheralClockConfig->peripheralClocks[i].frac);
723  }
724  }
725 }

727 /*FUNCTION**********************************************************************
728  *
729  * Function Name : CLOCK_SYS_SetSimConfiguration
730  * Description : This function configures the SIM block
731  *
732  * END**************************************************************************/
733 static void CLOCK_SYS_SetSimConfiguration(const sim_clock_config_t * simClockConfig)
734 {
735  DEV_ASSERT(simClockConfig != NULL);
736  uint8_t i;
737 
738  /* ClockOut settings. */
739  if (simClockConfig->clockOutConfig.initialize)
740  {
741  SIM_SetClockout(SIM, simClockConfig->clockOutConfig.enable, simClockConfig->clockOutConfig.source, simClockConfig->clockOutConfig.divider);
742  }
743 
744  /* Low Power Clock settings from SIM. */
745  if (simClockConfig->lpoClockConfig.initialize)
746  {
747  SIM_SetLpoClocks(SIM,
748  simClockConfig->lpoClockConfig.enableLpo1k,
749  simClockConfig->lpoClockConfig.enableLpo32k,
750  simClockConfig->lpoClockConfig.sourceLpoClk,
751  simClockConfig->lpoClockConfig.sourceRtcClk);
752  }
753 
754  /* Platform Gate Clock settings. */
755  if (simClockConfig->platGateConfig.initialize)
756  {
757  SIM_SetMscmClockGate(SIM, simClockConfig->platGateConfig.enableMscm);
758  SIM_SetMpuClockGate(SIM, simClockConfig->platGateConfig.enableMpu);
759  SIM_SetDmaClockGate(SIM, simClockConfig->platGateConfig.enableDma);
760  SIM_SetErmClockGate(SIM, simClockConfig->platGateConfig.enableErm);
761  SIM_SetEimClockGate(SIM, simClockConfig->platGateConfig.enableEim);
762 #if defined (QuadSPI_INSTANCE_COUNT)
763  SIM_SetQspiIntRefClockGate(SIM, simClockConfig->qspiRefClkGating.enableQspiRefClk);
764 #endif
765  }
766 
767  /* TCLK Clock settings. */
768  if (simClockConfig->tclkConfig.initialize)
769  {
770  for (i = 0; i < NUMBER_OF_TCLK_INPUTS; i++)
771  {
772  g_TClkFreq[i] = simClockConfig->tclkConfig.tclkFreq[i];
773  }
774 
775  /* FTMOPT0 clock settings */
776  for (i = 0; i < FTM_INSTANCE_COUNT; i++)
777  {
778  SIM_SetExtPinSourceFtm(SIM, i, simClockConfig->tclkConfig.extPinSrc[i]);
779  }
780  }
781 
782 #if defined (S32K14x_SERIES)
783  /* Debug trace Clock settings. */
784  if (simClockConfig->traceClockConfig.initialize)
785  {
786  SIM_ClearTraceClockConfig(SIM);
787  SIM_SetTraceClockSource(SIM, simClockConfig->traceClockConfig.source);
788 
789  SIM_SetTraceClockConfig(SIM, false, 0U, 0U);
790 
791  if (simClockConfig->traceClockConfig.divEnable)
792  {
793  SIM_SetTraceClockConfig(SIM,
794  simClockConfig->traceClockConfig.divEnable,
795  simClockConfig->traceClockConfig.divider,
796  simClockConfig->traceClockConfig.divFraction);
797  }
798  }
799 #endif
800 }

1639 /*FUNCTION**********************************************************************
1640  * Function Name : CLOCK_SYS_GetOtherSimClockFreq
1641  * Description : This function returns the frequency of other clock from SIM
1642  * END**************************************************************************/
1643 static status_t CLOCK_SYS_GetOtherSimClockFreq(clock_names_t clockName,
1644  uint32_t * frequency)
1645 {
1646  status_t returnCode = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1647  uint32_t freq = 0 ;

1651  case SIM_CLKOUTSELL:

1666  freq = ((SIM_GetLpo32KStatus(SIM)) && (SIM_GetLpo1KStatus(SIM))) ? LPO_1K_FREQUENCY : 0UL;
1667  }
1668  break;
1669  case SIM_LPO_32K_CLK:
1670  if (PMC_GetLpoMode(PMC))
1671  {
1672  freq = SIM_GetLpo32KStatus(SIM) ? LPO_32K_FREQUENCY : 0UL;
1673  }
1674  break;

1676  if (PMC_GetLpoMode(PMC))
1677  {
1678  freq = LPO_128K_FREQUENCY;
1679  }
1680  break;
1681 #ifdef QuadSPI_INSTANCE_COUNT

1684  break;
1685  case QSPI_MODULE_CLK:
1686  freq = CLOCK_SYS_GetQspiIpgClk();
1687  break;
1688  case QSPI_MODULE_CLK_SFIF:
1689  freq = CLOCK_SYS_GetQspiIpgClkSfif();
1690  break;
1691  case QSPI_MODULE_CLK_2XSFIF:
1692  freq = CLOCK_SYS_GetQspiIpgClk2Xsfif();
1693  break;
1694 #endif
1695  default:
1696  returnCode = SIM_CheckPeripheralClockGate(clockName);
1697  break;
1698  }
1699  if(frequency != NULL)
1700  {
1701  *frequency = freq;
1702  }
1703 
1704  return returnCode;
1705 }

1707 /*FUNCTION**********************************************************************
1708  * Function Name : CLOCK_DRV_GetSysClockConfig
1709  * Description : get the system clock config
1710  * END**************************************************************************/
1711 static void CLOCK_DRV_GetSysClockConfig(scg_system_clock_mode_t sysClockMode,scg_system_clock_config_t *sysClkConfig_ptr)
1712 {
1713  static const scg_system_clock_div_t defSysClk[TMP_SYS_CLK_NO][TMP_SYS_DIV_NO] = TMP_SYSTEM_CLOCK_CONFIGS;
1714  bool getClockFreqState;
1715 
1716  if (CLOCK_SYS_GetFircFreq() != 0U)
1717  {
1718  getClockFreqState = true;
1719  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).src = SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_SRC_FIRC;
1720  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divCore = defSysClk[TMP_FIRC_CLK][TMP_SYS_DIV];
1721  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divBus = defSysClk[TMP_FIRC_CLK][TMP_BUS_DIV];
1722  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divSlow = defSysClk[TMP_FIRC_CLK][TMP_SLOW_DIV];
1723  }
1724 #if FEATURE_HAS_SPLL_CLK
1725  else if (CLOCK_SYS_GetSysPllFreq() != 0U)
1726  {
1727  getClockFreqState = true;
1728  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).src = SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_SRC_SYS_PLL;
1729  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divCore = defSysClk[TMP_SPLL_CLK][TMP_SYS_DIV];
1730  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divBus = defSysClk[TMP_SPLL_CLK][TMP_BUS_DIV];
1731  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divSlow = defSysClk[TMP_SPLL_CLK][TMP_SLOW_DIV];
1732  }
1733 #endif
1734  else if (CLOCK_SYS_GetSysOscFreq() != 0U)
1735  {
1736  getClockFreqState = true;
1737  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).src = SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_SRC_SYS_OSC;
1738  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divCore = defSysClk[TMP_SOSC_CLK][TMP_SYS_DIV];
1739  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divBus = defSysClk[TMP_SOSC_CLK][TMP_BUS_DIV];
1740  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divSlow = defSysClk[TMP_SOSC_CLK][TMP_SLOW_DIV];
1741  }
1742  else
1743  {
1744  getClockFreqState = false;
1745  }
1746  if (getClockFreqState == false)
1747  {
1748  if (CLOCK_SYS_GetSircFreq() != 0U)
1749  {
1750  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).src = SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_SRC_SIRC;
1751  if (sysClockMode == SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_MODE_VLPR)
1752  {
1753  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divCore = FEATURE_VLPR_SYS_CLK;
1754  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divBus = FEATURE_VLPR_BUS_CLK;
1755  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divSlow = FEATURE_VLPR_SLOW_CLK;
1756  }
1757  else
1758  {
1759  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divCore = defSysClk[TMP_SIRC_CLK][TMP_SYS_DIV];
1760  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divBus = defSysClk[TMP_SIRC_CLK][TMP_BUS_DIV];
1761  (*sysClkConfig_ptr).divSlow = defSysClk[TMP_SIRC_CLK][TMP_SLOW_DIV];
1762  }
1763  }
1764  else
1765  {
1766  /* Can't reach this point, at least one clock source is functional.
1767  * This code is written to avoid MISRA 15.7 (no 'else' at end of 'if ... else if' chain) */
1768  DEV_ASSERT(false);
1769  }
1770  }
1771 
1772  (void)sysClockMode;
1773 }

1775 /*FUNCTION**********************************************************************
1776  * Function Name : CLOCK_SYS_CheckPCCClock
1777  * Description : Checks if PCC clock name is valid and if the module is enabled.
1778  * END**************************************************************************/
1779 static status_t CLOCK_SYS_CheckPCCClock(clock_names_t clockName)
1780 {
1781  status_t returnCode = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1782 
1783  /* Invalid PCC clock names. */
1784  if ((clockName <= SIM_END_OF_CLOCKS) ||
1785  (clockName == PCC_END_OF_BUS_CLOCKS) ||
1786  (clockName == PCC_END_OF_SYS_CLOCKS) ||
1787  (clockName == PCC_END_OF_SLOW_CLOCKS) ||
1788  (clockName == PCC_END_OF_ASYNCH_DIV1_CLOCKS) ||
1789  (clockName == PCC_END_OF_ASYNCH_DIV2_CLOCKS))
1790  {
1791  returnCode = STATUS_UNSUPPORTED;
1792  }
1793  else if (PCC_GetClockMode(PCC, clockName) == false)
1794  {
1795  /* Module is not clocked. */
1796  returnCode = STATUS_MCU_GATED_OFF;
1797  }
1798  else
1799  {
1800  returnCode = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1801  }
1802 
1803  return returnCode;
1804 }

1806 /*FUNCTION**********************************************************************
1807  *
1808  * Function Name : CLOCK_SYS_GetPccClockFreq
1809  * Description : This function returns the clock frequency of peripheral functional clock.
1810  * END**************************************************************************/
1811 static status_t CLOCK_SYS_GetPccClockFreq(clock_names_t clockName,
1812  uint32_t * frequency)
1813 {
1814  status_t returnCode = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1815  uint32_t freq = 0U;
1816  uint32_t interfaceFreq = 0U;
1817 
1818  returnCode = CLOCK_SYS_CheckPCCClock(clockName);
1819 
1820  if (returnCode == STATUS_SUCCESS)
1821  {
1822  if ((peripheralFeaturesList[clockName] & HAS_INT_CLOCK_FROM_BUS_CLOCK) != 0U)
1823  {
1824  /* Check whether BUS CLOCK is clocked. */
1825  interfaceFreq = CLOCK_SYS_GetSystemClockFreq(SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_BUS);
1826  returnCode = (status_t)((interfaceFreq == 0U) ? STATUS_MCU_GATED_OFF : STATUS_SUCCESS);
1827  }
1828  else if ((peripheralFeaturesList[clockName] & HAS_INT_CLOCK_FROM_SYS_CLOCK) != 0U)
1829  {
1830  /* Check whether SYS CLOCK is clocked. */
1831  interfaceFreq = CLOCK_SYS_GetSystemClockFreq(SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_CORE);
1832  returnCode = (status_t)((interfaceFreq == 0U) ? STATUS_MCU_GATED_OFF : STATUS_SUCCESS);
1833  }
1834  else if ((peripheralFeaturesList[clockName] & HAS_INT_CLOCK_FROM_SLOW_CLOCK) != 0U)
1835  {
1836  /* Check whether SLOW CLOCK is clocked. */
1837  interfaceFreq = CLOCK_SYS_GetSystemClockFreq(SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_SLOW);
1838  returnCode = (status_t)((interfaceFreq == 0U) ? STATUS_MCU_GATED_OFF : STATUS_SUCCESS);
1839  }
1840  else
1841  { /* It's an issue in peripheral features list, each peripheral must have one interface clock. */
1842  DEV_ASSERT(false);
1843  }
1844 
1845  if (returnCode == STATUS_SUCCESS)
1846  {
1847  /* Check whether peripheral has protocol clock (functional clock) */
1848  if ((peripheralFeaturesList[clockName] & (HAS_PROTOCOL_CLOCK_FROM_ASYNC1 | HAS_PROTOCOL_CLOCK_FROM_ASYNC2)) != 0U)
1849  {
1850  if ((peripheralFeaturesList[clockName] & HAS_PROTOCOL_CLOCK_FROM_ASYNC1) != 0U)
1851  {
1852  /* Check whether the functional clock is clocked */
1853  freq = CLOCK_SYS_GetPeripheralClock(clockName, SCG_ASYNC_CLOCK_DIV1);
1854  }
1855 
1856  if ((peripheralFeaturesList[clockName] & HAS_PROTOCOL_CLOCK_FROM_ASYNC2) != 0U)
1857  {
1858  /* Check whether the functional clock is clocked */
1859  freq = CLOCK_SYS_GetPeripheralClock(clockName, SCG_ASYNC_CLOCK_DIV2);
1860  }
1861 
1862  if (freq == 0U)
1863  {
1864  returnCode = STATUS_MCU_GATED_OFF;
1865  }
1866  }
1867  else
1868  {
1869 #if defined(QuadSPI_INSTANCE_COUNT)
1870  if (clockName == QSPI0_CLK)
1871  {
1872  freq = CLOCK_SYS_GetQspiIpgClk();
1873  }
1874  else
1875  {
1876  freq = interfaceFreq;
1877  }
1878 #else
1879  freq = interfaceFreq;
1880 #endif
1881  }
1882  }
1883  }
1884  (void)interfaceFreq;
1885 
1886  /* If frequency reference is provided, write this value */
1887  if (frequency != NULL)
1888  {
1889  *frequency = freq;
1890  }
1891 
1892  return returnCode;
1893 }

2037 /*FUNCTION**********************************************************************
2038  * Function Name : CLOCK_SYS_GetPeripheralClock
2039  * Description : Internal function used by CLOCK_SYS_GetPccClockFreq function
2040  * END**************************************************************************/
2041 
2042 static uint32_t CLOCK_SYS_GetPeripheralClock(clock_names_t clockName,
2043  scg_async_clock_type_t divider)
2044 {
2045  uint32_t frequency = 0;
2046  uint32_t fracValue = PCC_GetFracValueSel(PCC, clockName);
2047  uint32_t divValue = PCC_GetDividerSel(PCC, clockName);
2048 
2049  /* Check division factor */
2050  if (((uint32_t)fracValue) <= ((uint32_t)divValue))
2051  {
2052  /* Check clock gate */
2053  if (PCC_GetClockMode(PCC, clockName))
2054  {
2055  /* Check clock source */
2056  switch (PCC_GetClockSourceSel(PCC, clockName))
2057  {
2058  case (uint32_t)CLK_SRC_SOSC:
2059  frequency = CLOCK_SYS_GetSysAsyncFreq(SOSC_CLK, divider);
2060  break;
2061  case (uint32_t)CLK_SRC_SIRC:
2062  frequency = CLOCK_SYS_GetSysAsyncFreq(SIRC_CLK, divider);
2063  break;
2064  case (uint32_t)CLK_SRC_FIRC:
2065  frequency = CLOCK_SYS_GetSysAsyncFreq(FIRC_CLK, divider);
2066  break;
2067 #if FEATURE_HAS_SPLL_CLK
2068  case (uint32_t)CLK_SRC_SPLL:
2069  frequency = CLOCK_SYS_GetSysAsyncFreq(SPLL_CLK, divider);
2070  break;
2071 #endif
2072 #if FEATURE_HAS_LPO_PERIPHERAL_CLOCK_SOURCE
2073  case (uint32_t)CLK_SRC_LPO:
2074  (void)CLOCK_SYS_GetSimClockFreq(SIM_LPO_CLK, &frequency);
2075  divValue = 0U;
2076  break;
2077 #endif
2078  default:
2079  (void)CLOCK_SYS_GetFtmOptionFreq(clockName, &frequency);
2080  divValue = 0U;
2081  break;
2082  }
2083 
2084  frequency = frequency / (divValue + 1U);
2085  frequency = frequency * (fracValue + 1U);
2086  }
2087  }
2088 
2089  return frequency;
2090 }

2774  * (use one of the following sources: SPLL, SOSC, SIRC)
2775  * Assume that a temporary clock is not found status = ERROR. */
2776  status = STATUS_ERROR;
2777

2786  status = CLOCK_SYS_TransitionSystemClock(&sysClockConfig);
2787  }
2788 #endif
2789

2794  sysClockConfig.divCore = tmpSysClk[TMP_SOSC_CLK][TMP_SYS_DIV];
2795  sysClockConfig.divBus = tmpSysClk[TMP_SOSC_CLK][TMP_BUS_DIV];

2803  {
2804  sysClockConfig.src = SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_SRC_SIRC;
2805  sysClockConfig.divCore = tmpSysClk[TMP_SIRC_CLK][TMP_SYS_DIV];
2806  sysClockConfig.divBus = tmpSysClk[TMP_SIRC_CLK][TMP_BUS_DIV];
2807  sysClockConfig.divSlow = tmpSysClk[TMP_SIRC_CLK][TMP_SLOW_DIV];
2808  status = CLOCK_SYS_TransitionSystemClock(&sysClockConfig);
2809  }
2810 
2811  /* Transitioned to a temporary system clock source. */
2812  if (status == STATUS_SUCCESS)
2813  {
2814  /* Configure the remaining clock source (FIRC). */
2815  status = CLOCK_SYS_ConfigureFIRC(scgConfig->fircConfig.initialize, &scgConfig->fircConfig);
2816 
2817  if (status == STATUS_SUCCESS)
2818  {
2819  /* Transition to the next system clock source. */
2820  sysClockConfig.src = nextSysClockConfig->src;
2821  sysClockConfig.divCore = nextSysClockConfig->divCore;
2822  sysClockConfig.divBus = nextSysClockConfig->divBus;
2823  sysClockConfig.divSlow = nextSysClockConfig->divSlow;
2824  status = CLOCK_SYS_TransitionSystemClock(&sysClockConfig);
2825  }
2826  }
2827  }
2828  else
2829  { /* Transition to the next system clock source. */
2830  sysClockConfig.src = nextSysClockConfig->src;
2831  sysClockConfig.divCore = nextSysClockConfig->divCore;
2832  sysClockConfig.divBus = nextSysClockConfig->divBus;
2833  sysClockConfig.divSlow = nextSysClockConfig->divSlow;
2834  status = CLOCK_SYS_TransitionSystemClock(&sysClockConfig);
2835 
2836  if (status == STATUS_SUCCESS)
2837  {
2838  /* Configure the remaining clock source (FIRC) */
2839  status = CLOCK_SYS_ConfigureFIRC(scgConfig->fircConfig.initialize, &scgConfig->fircConfig);
2840  }
2841  }
2842  }
2843 
2844  return status;
2845 }

2933 /*FUNCTION**********************************************************************
2934  * Function Name : CLOCK_SYS_SetSystemClockConfig
2935  * Description : This function sets the system configuration for the specified mode.
2936  * END**************************************************************************/
2937 static status_t CLOCK_SYS_SetSystemClockConfig(scg_system_clock_mode_t mode,
2938  scg_system_clock_config_t const * config)
2939 {
2940  status_t status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
2941  uint32_t srcFreq = 0U;
2942 
2943  /* The maximum clock frequencies of system clocks in all power modes */
2944  static const uint32_t maxSysClksInVLPR[MODES_MAX_NO][SYS_CLK_MAX_NO] = CLOCK_MAX_FREQUENCIES_VLPR_MODE;
2945  static const uint32_t maxSysClksInRUN[MODES_MAX_NO][SYS_CLK_MAX_NO] = CLOCK_MAX_FREQUENCIES_RUN_MODE;
2946 #if FEATURE_HAS_HIGH_SPEED_RUN_MODE
2947  static const uint32_t maxSysClksInHSRUN[MODES_MAX_NO][SYS_CLK_MAX_NO] = CLOCK_MAX_FREQUENCIES_HSRUN_MODE;
2948 #endif
2949  const uint32_t sysFreqMul = ((uint32_t)config->divCore) + 1UL;
2950  const uint32_t busFreqMul = (((uint32_t)config->divCore) + 1UL) * (((uint32_t)config->divBus) + 1UL);
2951  const uint32_t slowFreqMul = (((uint32_t)config->divCore) + 1UL) * (((uint32_t)config->divSlow) + 1UL);
2952 
2953  DEV_ASSERT(mode != SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_MODE_CURRENT);
2954 
2955  srcFreq = CLOCK_SYS_GetSrcFreq(config->src);
2956  srcFreq >>= 4U;
2957 
2958  switch (mode)
2959  {
2960  case SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_MODE_RUN:
2961  /* Verify the frequencies of sys, bus and slow clocks. */
2962  if ((srcFreq > (sysFreqMul * (maxSysClksInRUN[(uint32_t)config->src][CORE_CLK_INDEX] >> 4U))) || /* Sys(core) clock */
2963  (srcFreq > (busFreqMul * (maxSysClksInRUN[(uint32_t)config->src][BUS_CLK_INDEX] >> 4U))) || /* Bus clock */
2964  (srcFreq > (slowFreqMul * (maxSysClksInRUN[(uint32_t)config->src][SLOW_CLK_INDEX] >> 4U)))) /* Slow clock */
2965  {
2966  /* Configuration for the next system clock source is not valid. */
2967  status = STATUS_ERROR;
2968  }
2969  else
2970  {
2971  SCG_SetRunClockControl(SCG, (uint32_t)config->src, (uint32_t)config->divCore, (uint32_t)config->divBus, (uint32_t)config->divSlow);
2972  }
2973  break;
2974  case SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_MODE_VLPR:
2975  DEV_ASSERT(SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_SRC_SIRC == config->src);
2976  /* Verify the frequencies of sys, bus and slow clocks. */
2977  if ((srcFreq > (sysFreqMul * (maxSysClksInVLPR[(uint32_t)config->src][CORE_CLK_INDEX] >> 4U))) || /* Sys(core) clock */
2978  (srcFreq > (busFreqMul * (maxSysClksInVLPR[(uint32_t)config->src][BUS_CLK_INDEX] >> 4U))) || /* Bus clock */
2979  (srcFreq > (slowFreqMul * (maxSysClksInVLPR[(uint32_t)config->src][SLOW_CLK_INDEX] >> 4U)))) /* Slow clock */
2980  {
2981  /* Configuration for the next system clock source is not valid. */
2982  status = STATUS_ERROR;
2983  }
2984  else
2985  {
2986  SCG_SetVlprClockControl(SCG, (uint32_t)config->src, (uint32_t)config->divCore, (uint32_t)config->divBus, (uint32_t)config->divSlow);
2987  }
2988  break;
2989 #if FEATURE_HAS_HIGH_SPEED_RUN_MODE
2990  case SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_MODE_HSRUN:
2991  DEV_ASSERT((SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_SRC_FIRC == config->src) || ( SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_SRC_SYS_PLL == config->src));
2992  /* Verify the frequencies of sys, bus and slow clocks. */
2993  if ((srcFreq > (sysFreqMul * (maxSysClksInHSRUN[(uint32_t)config->src][CORE_CLK_INDEX] >> 4U))) || /* Sys(core) clock */
2994  (srcFreq > (busFreqMul * (maxSysClksInHSRUN[(uint32_t)config->src][BUS_CLK_INDEX] >> 4U))) || /* Bus clock */
2995  (srcFreq > (slowFreqMul * (maxSysClksInHSRUN[(uint32_t)config->src][SLOW_CLK_INDEX] >> 4U)))) /* Slow clock */
2996  {
2997  /* Configuration for the next system clock source is not valid. */
2998  status = STATUS_ERROR;
2999  }
3000  else
3001  {
3002  SCG_SetHsrunClockControl(SCG, (uint32_t)config->src, (uint32_t)config->divCore, (uint32_t)config->divBus, (uint32_t)config->divSlow);
3003  }
3004  break;
3005 #endif
3006  default:
3007  /* Invalid mode */
3008  DEV_ASSERT(false);
3009  break;
3010  }
3011  return status;
3012 }

3014 /*FUNCTION**********************************************************************

3016  * Description : Gets SCG asynchronous clock frequency from a clock source.
3017  * END**************************************************************************/
3018 static uint32_t CLOCK_SYS_GetSysAsyncFreq(clock_names_t clockSource,
3019  scg_async_clock_type_t type)
3020 {
3021  uint32_t freq, div = 0U;
3022 
3023  switch (type)

3654  /* The power mode is not provided, the current one will be used by default. */
3655  if (mode == NULL)
3656  {
3657  sysClockMode = currentSysClockMode;
3658  }
3659  else
3660  {
3661  sysClockMode = CLOCK_SYS_GetSysClockMode(*mode);
3662  }
3663 
3664  /* System clock configuration is not provided, a default one will be used. */
3665  if (sysClkConfig == NULL)
3666  {
3667  /* Find a valid clock source. */
3668  CLOCK_DRV_GetSysClockConfig(sysClockMode,&sysClockConfig);
3669  }
3670  else
3671  {
3672  /* The system clock source from input configuration structure must be valid. */
3673  DEV_ASSERT((CLOCK_SYS_GetSircFreq() != 0U) || (sysClkConfig->src != SIRC_CLK));
3674  DEV_ASSERT((CLOCK_SYS_GetFircFreq() != 0U) || (sysClkConfig->src != FIRC_CLK));
3675  DEV_ASSERT((CLOCK_SYS_GetSysOscFreq() != 0U) || (sysClkConfig->src != SOSC_CLK));
3676 #if FEATURE_HAS_SPLL_CLK
3677  DEV_ASSERT((CLOCK_SYS_GetSysPllFreq() != 0U) || (sysClkConfig->src != SPLL_CLK));
3678 #endif
3679 
3680  sysClockConfig.src = CLOCK_SYS_GetSysClockSource(sysClkConfig->src);
3681 
3682  DEV_ASSERT(sysClkConfig->dividers[0U] != 0U);
3683  DEV_ASSERT(sysClkConfig->dividers[1U] != 0U);
3684  DEV_ASSERT(sysClkConfig->dividers[2U] != 0U);
3685 
3686  sysClockConfig.divCore = sysClkDivMappings[sysClkConfig->dividers[0U]];
3687  sysClockConfig.divBus = sysClkDivMappings[sysClkConfig->dividers[1U]];
3688  sysClockConfig.divSlow = sysClkDivMappings[sysClkConfig->dividers[2U]];
3689  }
3690 
3691  /* System clock is configured in the current mode,
3692  * set configuration and wait until the system clock is changed. */
3693  if (sysClockMode == currentSysClockMode)
3694  {
3695  retCode = CLOCK_SYS_TransitionSystemClock(&sysClockConfig);
3696  }
3697  /* System clock is not configured in the current mode, just set configuration. */
3698  else
3699  {
3700  retCode = CLOCK_SYS_SetSystemClockConfig(sysClockMode,&sysClockConfig);
3701  }
3702  return retCode;
3703 }

3706 /*FUNCTION**********************************************************************
3707  *
3708  * Function Name : CLOCK_DRV_GetSystemClockSource
3709  * Description : This function gets the current system clock source
3710  *
3711  * Implements CLOCK_DRV_GetSystemClockSource_Activity
3712  * END**************************************************************************/
3713 void CLOCK_DRV_GetSystemClockSource(sys_clk_config_t *sysClkConfig)
3714 {

3725  }
3726  break;
3727  case SCG_SYSTEM_CLOCK_SRC_FIRC:

3729  sysClkConfig->src = FIRC_CLK;
3730  }
3731  break;

3734  {
3735  sysClkConfig->src = SPLL_CLK;
3736  }
3737  break;
3738 #endif
3739  default:
3740  {
3741  /* Invalid system clock source. */
3742  DEV_ASSERT(false);
3743  sysClkConfig->src = SIRC_CLK;
3744  }
3745  break;
3746  }
3747 
3748  /* Core divider */

3750 
3751  /* Bus divider */

3753 
3754  /* Slow divider */
3755  sysClkConfig->dividers[2U] = (uint16_t) (SCG_GetCurrentSlowClockDividerRatio(SCG) + 1U);
3756 }

4163 /*FUNCTION**********************************************************************
4164  *
4165  * Function Name : CLOCK_SYS_UpdateConfiguration
4166  * Description : Send notification and change system clock configuration.
4167  * This function sends the notification to all callback functions, if all
4168  * callbacks return OK or forceful policy is used, this function will change
4169  * system clock configuration. The function should be called only on run mode.
4170  *
4171  * Implements CLOCK_SYS_UpdateConfiguration_Activity
4172  *END**************************************************************************/
4173 status_t CLOCK_SYS_UpdateConfiguration(uint8_t targetConfigIndex,
4174  clock_manager_policy_t policy)
4175 {
4176  uint8_t callbackIdx;
4177  bool successfulSetConfig; /* SetConfiguraiton status */
4178  status_t ret = STATUS_SUCCESS;
4179  status_t callbackState = STATUS_SUCCESS;
4180  const clock_manager_callback_user_config_t * callbackConfig;
4181  clock_notify_struct_t notifyStruct;
4182 
4183  DEV_ASSERT(targetConfigIndex < g_clockState.clockConfigNum); /* Clock configuration index is out of range. */
4184 
4185  notifyStruct.targetClockConfigIndex = targetConfigIndex;
4186  notifyStruct.policy = policy;
4187 
4188  /* Disable interrupts */
4189  INT_SYS_DisableIRQGlobal();
4190  /* Set errorcallbackindex as callbackNum, which means no callback error now.*/
4191  g_clockState.errorCallbackIndex = g_clockState.callbackNum;
4192 
4193  /* First step: Send "BEFORE" notification. */
4194  notifyStruct.notifyType = CLOCK_MANAGER_NOTIFY_BEFORE;
4195 
4196  /* Send notification to all callback. */
4197  for (callbackIdx=0; callbackIdx<g_clockState.callbackNum; callbackIdx++)
4198  {
4199  callbackConfig = g_clockState.callbackConfig[callbackIdx];
4200  if ((callbackConfig) &&
4201  (callbackConfig->callbackType != CLOCK_MANAGER_CALLBACK_AFTER))
4202  {
4203  if (STATUS_SUCCESS !=
4204  (*callbackConfig->callback)(&notifyStruct,
4205  callbackConfig->callbackData))
4206  {
4207  g_clockState.errorCallbackIndex = callbackIdx;
4208 
4209  if (CLOCK_MANAGER_POLICY_AGREEMENT == policy)
4210  {
4211  /* Save the error callback index. */
4212  ret = STATUS_MCU_NOTIFY_BEFORE_ERROR;
4213  break;
4214  }
4215  }
4216  }
4217  }
4218 
4219  /* If all callback success or forceful policy is used. */
4220  if ((STATUS_SUCCESS == ret) ||
4221  (policy == CLOCK_MANAGER_POLICY_FORCIBLE))
4222  {
4223  /* clock mode switch. */
4224  ret = CLOCK_SYS_SetConfiguration(g_clockState.configTable[targetConfigIndex]);
4225  successfulSetConfig = (STATUS_SUCCESS == ret);
4226 
4227  g_clockState.curConfigIndex = targetConfigIndex;
4228  }
4229  else
4230  {
4231  /* Unsuccessful setConfiguration */
4232  successfulSetConfig = false;
4233  }
4234 
4235  if(successfulSetConfig){
4236  notifyStruct.notifyType = CLOCK_MANAGER_NOTIFY_AFTER;
4237 
4238  for (callbackIdx=0; callbackIdx<g_clockState.callbackNum; callbackIdx++)
4239  {
4240  callbackConfig = g_clockState.callbackConfig[callbackIdx];
4241  if ((callbackConfig) &&
4242  (callbackConfig->callbackType != CLOCK_MANAGER_CALLBACK_BEFORE))
4243  {
4244  callbackState = (*callbackConfig->callback)(&notifyStruct,
4245  callbackConfig->callbackData);
4246 
4247  }
4248  if (STATUS_SUCCESS != callbackState)
4249  {
4250  g_clockState.errorCallbackIndex = callbackIdx;
4251  if (CLOCK_MANAGER_POLICY_AGREEMENT == policy)
4252  {
4253  /* Save the error callback index. */
4254  ret = STATUS_MCU_NOTIFY_AFTER_ERROR;
4255  break;
4256  }
4257  }
4258  }
4259  }
4260  else /* Error occurs, need to send "RECOVER" notification. */
4261  {
4262  notifyStruct.notifyType = CLOCK_MANAGER_NOTIFY_RECOVER;
4263  for(;;)
4264  {
4265  callbackConfig = g_clockState.callbackConfig[callbackIdx];
4266  if (callbackConfig != NULL)
4267  {
